items.items: To record any non-operative procedure undertaken. Normally carried out in a clinic or ward setting and may be for therapeutic or diagnostic purposes.
Detailed structure describing the procedure performed.
The reason or indication for the procedure
An unplanned event prior to or related to the procedure, which may affect its execution e.g patient self-removed cannula.
The number of failed attempts to perform the procedure.
A link to a structured record e.g a diagnosis or problem describing the complication.
Reasons or indications for the procedure
An additional related taks that was performed . This will normally be another action but may be an instruction e.g On removal of a catheter, tip sent for microbiology.
Link to a record of the additional task.
Link to a record of an unplanned event.
To record any non-operative procedure undertaken. Normally carried out in a clinic or ward setting and may be for therapeutic or diagnostic purposes.!
Preparation steps taken prior to intubation.
The patient was monitored during preparation.
Details of any preparatory medications used.
Details of a prepatory medication, May be a simple text description or a a link to the actual medication record.
Details of the endotracheal tube used.
Single physical confirmation of tube placement.
Link to a record of medication delivered.
Complication arising from the endotracheal tube insertion procedure.
The number of times the laryngoscopic blade was inserted without a definite attempt to pass the tube.
A reason for the unsuccesful insertion of the endotracheal tube.
Details of formal confirmations of plkacment that have been prefromed and found adequate.
Single confirmation of correct tube placement.
Link to a record of a single confirmation of correct tube placement.
A chest x-ray confirms tube placement.
Endotracheal CO2 conforms correct tube placement.
Blood gas estimation confirms correct placement.
A gastric tube has been inserted.
A plan has been made for ongoing sedation.
